[python] fix race condition in builder

see #315

On network shares we observed race conditions, where the directory was
not yet fully written before calling make or cmake, thus the dependency
tracking failed and a rebuild was not properly triggered.

By explicitly syncing the directory we ensure that the files are in a
correct state.

[python] try to minimize the sync_dir calls

It seems that it is sufficient to call Builder.sync_dir in the
`exit_code == 2` branch. This reduces the number of syncs and should
help improve performance.

Revert this commit if the network race condition shows up again.

commits.message: Provide communicate() methods for OneDGrid and IdentityGrid

Add grid concepts


Add concepts for grid objects using concepts implementation from dune-common

Add entity and geometry concepts using C++20

* This depends on dune-common to support C++20 concepts
* Temporally, I used the namespace Dune::Concept::Concept. Is still to be discussed the final namespaces of these concepts.

Remove syntactic sugar and add expectation assertion for some concepts

The methods `is{Concept}` were just a syntactic sugar for the actual
evaluation of the concepts, there was no added value to them. Now, the methods introduced
now `expect{Concept}` assert that a concept is fullfiled. This is not a syntactic sugar
because the implemenation of the concept is forwared to either fallback implementation or
the C++20 concepts. In the first case, if a concept is not fullfiled, the compuler will just
issue an error on the static assert, while on the second, the compiler will indeed describe why
the concept was not fullfiled.
Add Intersection C++20 concept
Add Intersection iterator C++20 concept
Add IndexSet C++20 concept
Add IdSet C++20 concept
Add GridView C++20 concept

Add Grid C++20 concept

Add recursive Grid concept for different codim concepts in fallback implementation

Help compiler to issue more useful errors

Concepts do not allow recursion and hence, we have our recursive algorithm moved
into specializated templated integral constants. Unfortunately, when integral constants evaluate
to false, the compiler has no chance to inspect the underlying concepts and show a proper backtrace.
Now, in this commit, we just add a concept check on the codimension 0 because an error in any
codimension is very likely to show in others. This way users wil get better error messages if
the error happens for all codimensions. If the interface does not matche in other codimensions an
error is still produced without the concepts backtrace.

commits.message: Provide communicate() methods for OneDGrid and IdentityGrid

Add grid concepts


Add concepts for grid objects using concepts implementation from dune-common

Add entity and geometry concepts using C++20

* This depends on dune-common to support C++20 concepts
* Temporally, I used the namespace Dune::Concept::Concept. Is still to be discussed the final namespaces of these concepts.

Remove syntactic sugar and add expectation assertion for some concepts

The methods `is{Concept}` were just a syntactic sugar for the actual
evaluation of the concepts, there was no added value to them. Now, the methods introduced
now `expect{Concept}` assert that a concept is fullfiled. This is not a syntactic sugar
because the implemenation of the concept is forwared to either fallback implementation or
the C++20 concepts. In the first case, if a concept is not fullfiled, the compuler will just
issue an error on the static assert, while on the second, the compiler will indeed describe why
the concept was not fullfiled.

Add recursive Grid concept for different codim concepts in fallback implementation

Help compiler to issue more useful errors

Concepts do not allow recursion and hence, we have our recursive algorithm moved
into specializated templated integral constants. Unfortunately, when integral constants evaluate
to false, the compiler has no chance to inspect the underlying concepts and show a proper backtrace.
Now, in this commit, we just add a concept check on the codimension 0 because an error in any
codimension is very likely to show in others. This way users wil get better error messages if
the error happens for all codimensions. If the interface does not matche in other codimensions an
error is still produced without the concepts backtrace.

[python] fix race condition in builder

see #315

On network shares we observed race conditions, where the directory was
not yet fully written before calling make or cmake, thus the dependency
tracking failed and a rebuild was not properly triggered.

By explicitly syncing the directory we ensure that the files are in a
correct state.

[python] try to minimize the sync_dir calls

It seems that it is sufficient to call Builder.sync_dir in the
`exit_code == 2` branch. This reduces the number of syncs and should
help improve performance.

commits.message: Provide communicate() methods for OneDGrid and IdentityGrid

Add grid concepts


Add concepts for grid objects using concepts implementation from dune-common

Add entity and geometry concepts using C++20

* This depends on dune-common to support C++20 concepts
* Temporally, I used the namespace Dune::Concept::Concept. Is still to be discussed the final namespaces of these concepts.

Remove syntactic sugar and add expectation assertion for some concepts

The methods `is{Concept}` were just a syntactic sugar for the actual
evaluation of the concepts, there was no added value to them. Now, the methods introduced
now `expect{Concept}` assert that a concept is fullfiled. This is not a syntactic sugar
because the implemenation of the concept is forwared to either fallback implementation or
the C++20 concepts. In the first case, if a concept is not fullfiled, the compuler will just
issue an error on the static assert, while on the second, the compiler will indeed describe why
the concept was not fullfiled.
Add Intersection C++20 concept
Add Intersection iterator C++20 concept
Add IndexSet C++20 concept
Add IdSet C++20 concept
Add GridView C++20 concept

Add Grid C++20 concept

Add recursive Grid concept for different codim concepts in fallback implementation

Help compiler to issue more useful errors

Concepts do not allow recursion and hence, we have our recursive algorithm moved
into specializated templated integral constants. Unfortunately, when integral constants evaluate
to false, the compiler has no chance to inspect the underlying concepts and show a proper backtrace.
Now, in this commit, we just add a concept check on the codimension 0 because an error in any
codimension is very likely to show in others. This way users wil get better error messages if
the error happens for all codimensions. If the interface does not matche in other codimensions an
error is still produced without the concepts backtrace.
